-------------------------------------------------------------------
 Linux Commands Likely To Be Helpful
-------------------------------------------------------------------
 man <command>      Get info  how to use 'command'.  Short for manual.
 command -h         Get info how to use 'command'.  Sometimes ? or --help.

 gstat -a           See load on each cluster node.
 top                See list of running jobs and who is running them.
 df -H              See disk usage and availability.  /home and /stuff are what we care about.
 dsh -a <command>   Run a command on all nodes of a cluster.  See dsh -h for more.

 cd <directory>     Move to 'directory'.
 ls                 See content of a directory (see man page).
 pwd                See path of current directory.
 ps                 Get info about running processes (see man page).

 scp                A command line version of FileZilla (see man page).
